results.deck: Human Entertainment (ヒューマン株式会社 Hyūman Kabushiki Gaisha) was a Japanese computer and video game developer and publisher.
results.description:
The company was known for originating the popular Fire Pro Wrestling series of wrestling games, as well as the Super Formation Soccer and Final Match Tennis sports games, and Human Grand Prix driving/racing games.

They are also known for their more innovative titles that are considered ahead of their time, including the first music rhythm game Dance Aerobics (1987); early survival horror games such as Laplace no Ma (1987) and the Clock Tower series; early survival adventure games such as SOS (1993) and The Firemen series; and their swan song, the ambitious open-world sandbox adventure Mizzurna Falls (1998).

The company eventually folded in 1999. Former members later went on to form different development teams, including Nude Maker, Sandlot, and Spike. The most notable offspring is Grasshopper Manufacture, founded by former Human Entertainment member Goichi Suda along with other former members.
